1.What ſhall be ſaid a Seſſion of Parliament. If a Parliament be Aſſembled, and divers Orders made,
and a Writ of Error brought, and a Record delivered to the
higher Houſe, and divers Bills agreed, but no Bills Signed;
That this is but a Convention, and no Parliament or Seſſion;
as it was Anno 12 Jac. in which (as it was affirmed by them
which had ſeen the Roll) it is entred that it is not any Seſſion;
or Parliament, becauſe that no Bill was ſigned, vide 33. H. 6.
Brook Parliament. 86. Every Seſſion in which the King ſigns
Bills is a Parliament.
